<div class="flex flex-1 flex-wrap max-w-full lg:max-w-[80%] mx-auto min-h-screen">
    <%- include('../partials/sidebar.ejs')%>
    <div class="grow lg:max-w-[60%] max-w-full lg:border-x-[1px] lg:overflow-y-scroll">
        <div class="text-4xl pt-10 px-6 font-bold pb-4">Methodology</div>
        <div class="text-xl pt-6 px-6 font-bold pb-2">
            Summary
        </div>
        <div class="text-md pt-4 px-6 pr-16 text-gray-700">To generate this simulation data, we use the national weather serviceâ€™s damage assessment toolkit to determine where and when
            tornado strikes occurred. This data is served in 3 forms: polygons, lines, and points.
            We process these data points with our algorithm, which gives us a map of all the policyholders receiving payouts, and the respective values of those payouts.
        </div>
        <div class="text-xl pt-6 px-6 font-bold pb-2">
            Generating Sample Homeowners
        </div>
        <div class="text-md pt-4 px-6 pr-16 text-gray-700">For this model, Sola generated around 40,000 points per state that simulate sample Sola policyholders. For each state, the same set of points
            is used for each year. Points were generated using the following method:
        </div>
        <div class="text-md pt-4 px-6 pr-16 ml-8 text-gray-700 list-decimal">
            <li>Use RapidAPI to represent the zip code as a polygon</li>
            <li>Generate x number of points randomly based on population density of the zip code</li>
            <li>Repeat for every zip code</li>
            <li>Repeat for every year</li>
        </div>
        <div class="text-xl pt-6 px-6 font-bold pb-2">
            Calculating Sample Payouts
        </div>
        <div class="text-md pt-4 px-6 pr-16 text-gray-700">To calculate sample payouts for this model, Sola used the DAT from the NWS. Payouts were calculated using
            the following method:
        </div>
        <div class="text-md pt-4 px-6 pr-16 ml-8 text-gray-700 list-decimal">
            <li>Query polygons for a month from the DAT </li>
            <li>Combine polygons into a multipolygon</li>
            <li>Repeat for every month</li>
            <li>Repeat with lines and points, combining them into multilinestrings and multipoints respectively</li>
            <li>Query sample policyholders based on damage within the multipolygon, 500ft of the multilinestring, and 500ft of multipoints</li>
            <li>Filter out duplicates</li>
            <li>Generate visualization of points and payouts</li>
            <li>Generate statistics</li>
            <li>Repeat for every state</li>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
